JOHANNESBURG - Mining company AngloGold Ashanti said on Monday it chief executive officer Srinivasan Venkatakrishnan had resigned, after accepting an offer to become CEO diversified resources group Vedanta. "A global search for the new CEO is underway, with a sub-committee of the Board formed to evaluate internal and external candidates. It is the Board’s intention that a successor will have been identified before Venkat’s departure," AngloGold Ashanti said in a statement. - African News Agency (ANA)